# Changes in v.0.20.0

The notions of front-end and back-end were rather hazy and confusing. So quite a lot of the Go code has been reorganised in the hope of making the program a bit easier to understand.

The supported input structures (currently "DB" and `FET`) are accessed via the `TtSource` interface and the output structures (currently only `FET`) via the `TtBackend` interface, both defined in "autotimetable/interface.go". This should work in a way independent of the actual implementations of these interfaces. Because of the special handling of `FET` file input (the back-end uses the structures of the source rather than building new `FET` structures), the independence is not fully achieved, but the situation should be a lot better than in previous versions. For other input sources, it should be possible to build the back-end structures using the `TtSource` interface, without needing further access to the internal source structures.

A further change is that it is now possible to have a source constraint map to multiple back-end constraints. This possibility is not used at present, though. A many-to-one constraint mapping is likely to be rather unmanageable, so I probably won't consider it.

Slight changes have been made to the result output (JSON). The most significant is probably the additional information provided in the Activities list. This should make reading the file a bit easier.
